  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chief Financial Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Familiar with the accounting, tax planning, financial support, and effective advisory for bulk commodity trade and supply chain;</li><li>Capable of treasury management in overseas and cross-border trade, responsible for the comprehensive management of funds and assets;</li><li>Able to develop funding channels domestically and internationally, with a realistic control over front-office business risks;</li><li>Responsible for the audit work of the entire group;<br />Capable of reviewing and analyzing group financial statements.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.</li><li>A minimum of 10 years of relevant experience in commodity trade.</li><li>A proven track record in the Financial Services sector, having held positions such as CFO, Finance Manager, or Finance Controller, with specific experience in Commodities trading.</li><li>Comprehensive knowledge of corporate financial law and practices related to risk management.</li><li>Demonstrated leadership skills, with the ability to work independently and collaboratively as part of a team.</li><li>Substantial exposure to methods involving data analysis and forecasting.</li><li>Outstanding interpersonal and communication abilities.</li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Careerstar International Pte Ltd</strong></p><p>EA License No: 03C3254</p><p>EA Personnel No: R23115696</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Chin Lee Wei</p>",
